ng of high and low intensity conflict, the involvement of media and human rights movements, and the martial administration of civilian populations. Exploring the broad social and organizational features of these militaries, this volume sets forth new analytical tools to understand the peculiarities of irregular warfare in the post-Cold War era. These critical concepts include loose coupling between units, organizations that mediate between ground forces and civilian environments, and the militarization of civilian environments in urban warfare  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAl-Aqsa Intifada, 2000-xSocial aspects. 0aAl-Aqsa Intifada, 2000-. 0aAl-Aqsa Intifada, 2000-2005xSocial aspects. 0aAl-Aqsa Intifada, 2000-2005. 0aCombatxSocial aspectszIsraelxHistoryy21st century. 0aCombatxSocial aspectszWest BankxHistoryy21st century. 0aSoldierszIsraelxSocial conditionsy21st century. 0aUrban warfarezIsraelxHistoryy21st century. 0aUrban warfarezWest BankxHistoryy21st century. 0aWar and societyzIsraelxHistoryy21st century. 4aArea Studies : Israel Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 4aSociology : Sociobiology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aBen-Shalom, Uzi, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLerer, Zeev, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438431864423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438431864/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles